{% extends "layouts/doc-layout" %}

{% block title %}Raw Filter - Wisp Template Documentation{% end %}

{% block body %}
<h1>Raw Filter</h1>

<p>Marks a string as safe HTML, bypassing the auto-escaping that normally protects against XSS.</p>

<h2>Syntax</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ value | raw }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>

<h2>Examples</h2>
<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ "<strong>bold</strong>" | raw }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> <strong>bold</strong> (rendered as bold HTML)</p>

<pre><code>{% raw %}
{{ trustedHtmlContent | raw }}
{% endraw %}</code></pre>
<p><strong>Output:</strong> The HTML is rendered as-is without escaping.</p>

<h2>Notes</h2>
<p><strong>Security warning:</strong> Never use <code>raw</code> on user-provided content. This filter completely bypasses HTML auto-escaping, which means any HTML or JavaScript in the value will be rendered directly in the browser. Only use it on content you fully control and trust, such as pre-sanitized HTML from your own application code.</p>

<p>By default, Wisp escapes all output to prevent XSS attacks. The <code>raw</code> filter opts out of this protection for the specific value.</p>

<h2>See Also</h2>
<ul>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/escape">escape</a></li>
  <li><a href="/docs/filters/escape_once">escape_once</a></li>
  <li><a href="/docs/templates/security">Security</a></li>
</ul>
{% end %}
